Instantaneous network model diagnostics - test risk group tersm

This file shows diagnostics for instantaneous network models. Here we test whether we can fit a model with only edges + nodefactor(“riskg”) to see if the risk group definitions are problematic independent of other terms in the model. We try fitting these: 1) using the original target statistics from the data, where the lowest groups have 0 instantaneous partnerships. This model includes the offset for role class. 2) With a dummy network of 10,000 with four equally sized risk groups. The total number of edges corresponds to that in the data, but the target stats for nodefactor(riskg) are set arbitrarily and range from 0 to >80% of total degree. In this first model, the highest group is the reference level and we do not include an offset for role class. 3) Using the dummy network and target statistics defined above but with the lowest quartile set to the reference group. 4) Using model 2 but including the offsets for role class.
